        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 11 at 3:26PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 326 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Forest Acres, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cane Savannah, Arcadia Lakes, Dalzell, Cayce, Irmo, St. Andrews,
Oakland, Lexington, Cayce Riverwalk, Columbia International
University, Pine Ridge, Wateree River Correctional Institution,
Stateburg, Dixiana, Harbison State Forest, Seven Oaks, Olympia,
Dentsville, Oak Grove, and Sesquicentennial State Park.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 126 between mile markers 0 and 3.
Interstate 20 in South Carolina between mile markers 51 and 82.
Interstate 26 between mile markers 102 and 122.
Interstate 77 between mile markers 0 and 19.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
